[This report was also referred to ProMED-mail by Dr. Jack Soo
<kyip@asia.com>. The text is ambiguous and it is not entirely clear that
the Indore genotype of poliomyelitis virus was in fact the strain isolated
from the patient in Qinhai. It is clear that cross-border cooperation will
be an increasing necessity in the final stages of the global eradication of
poliomyelitis - Mod. CP
